<div id="review_3233019429" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3233019429" />
    <a title="Lori Downs" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/14976870-lori-downs"><img alt="Lori Downs" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1514602175p2/14976870.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3233019429?book_show_action=true">Sep 13, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lori Downs" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lori Downs" href="/user/show/14976870-lori-downs">Lori Downs</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3233019429" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5431996342787818423">This story was heartwarming; it was heartbreaking at times, but a wonderful story of true love. I liked how it went back between present day and the early 1950’s; the author did a great job describing how life was during this time period. I liked all the main characters and I really enjoyed the descriptions of the places in the book. There was a little mystery of what happened to Hal and Rhonda that I was anxious to find out about. Reading the letters was quite interesting. The modern day story </span>
  <span id="freeText5431996342787818423" style="display:none">This story was heartwarming; it was heartbreaking at times, but a wonderful story of true love. I liked how it went back between present day and the early 1950’s; the author did a great job describing how life was during this time period. I liked all the main characters and I really enjoyed the descriptions of the places in the book. There was a little mystery of what happened to Hal and Rhonda that I was anxious to find out about. Reading the letters was quite interesting. The modern day story was good as well; as well finding out all the similarities between Rhonda and Vanessa, the woman who finds Rhonda’s old letters. Overall, it was an enjoyable story. I would like to read more from this author.</span>
