        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/34993287-the-summer-letters">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4130256597" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1735896445470160819"><strong>The Summer Letter</strong><br/><br/>This story begins in 2017 with the main character Vanessa who decides to rent a cabin on the beach in Massachusetts for the summer after her brutal divorce. While she is in the cottage she finds a coffee tin full of letters that goes back to life after WWII in 1953. She starts reading these letters and gets very involved in the two main characters who wrote the letters. In the meantime she meets a chap called Matthew who actually runs into her on his bike. While she is busy read</span>
  <span id="freeText1735896445470160819" style="display:none"><strong>The Summer Letter</strong><br /><br />This story begins in 2017 with the main character Vanessa who decides to rent a cabin on the beach in Massachusetts for the summer after her brutal divorce. While she is in the cottage she finds a coffee tin full of letters that goes back to life after WWII in 1953. She starts reading these letters and gets very involved in the two main characters who wrote the letters. In the meantime she meets a chap called Matthew who actually runs into her on his bike. While she is busy reading the letters, she herself starts to date, and gets so involved in the worrisome letters that she gets Matt her new friend to see if the characters in the letters ever stay together, and how their lives turned out. The story goes back an forth between 1953 and 2017. This book keeps you on your toes as the reader just gets into the facts of 1953, then you are bounced forward again to 2017. I would give this book a 4 star. The outcome of the book is interesting.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1735896445470160819" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


