  <span id="freeText1913368429569563632" style="display:none">This is such a charming book, the kind I used to read years ago but sadly no longer seem the vogue in the modern literary climate. It’s one I would describe as a perfect summer read, and suitably that’s how the story starts at the beginning of the summer. <br />The characters of Vanessa and Matt are written very well, and there’s an immediate warmth you feel towards them as their story begins to unfurl. Not satisfied with leaving readers only with this story there is another wrapped up in the past about another couple, Rhonda and Hal. Obviously I won’t give away any spoilers about how things come about, in the current day or the past, but it is a really great read to treat yourself with a glass of wine and putting your feet up on a lazy day. I thoroughly enjoyed it and will read more by this formidable authorial partnership soon.<br /></span>
