    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2033535631" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7589796307944126290">I have a special place in my heart for stories that jump from the past to present in a smooth and meaningful way. When done right, it can add so much depth to the story. Elyse Douglas did just that in The Summer Letters. I found the story to be lovely and I became caught up in the passionate relationship between Hal and Rhonda. Their romance is told through 60-year-old letters that are found in a cottage by its current resident, Vanessa. The character development was great, I remained intrigued,</span>
  <span id="freeText7589796307944126290" style="display:none">I have a special place in my heart for stories that jump from the past to present in a smooth and meaningful way. When done right, it can add so much depth to the story. Elyse Douglas did just that in The Summer Letters. I found the story to be lovely and I became caught up in the passionate relationship between Hal and Rhonda. Their romance is told through 60-year-old letters that are found in a cottage by its current resident, Vanessa. The character development was great, I remained intrigued, and would recommend this to anyone who enjoys an emotional love story. </span>
  <a data-text-id="7589796307944126290" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

