<div id="review_3443049227" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3443049227" />
    <a title="Melissa" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/60515136-melissa"><img alt="Melissa" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1551324856p2/60515136.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3443049227?book_show_action=true">Jul 14, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Melissa" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Melissa" href="/user/show/60515136-melissa">Melissa</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/34993287-the-summer-letters">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3443049227" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14022536249943638447"><strong>The Summer Letters</strong><br/><br/>When Vanessa moved into a beach house she started cleaning and came upon a tin can with letters in it. After reading them she wanted to find out what had happened to the couple from 1953 that loved each other so very much. After some digging she finally found the lady 87 years old in an assisted home. Her husband had died but she was very great full to get her letters.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


